  <title>pyrolysis</title>
  <termversion>2.3.3</termversion>
  <lastupdated>2014-02-24</lastupdated>
  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>Thermolysis, usually associated with exposure to a high temperature.</text>
      <notes>
        <item>The term generally refers to reaction in an inert environment.</item>
        <item>Pyrolysis is the commonly used term for a high-temperature treatment that converts a ceramic precursor to a ceramic.</item>
        <item>Modified from previous definition. The definition proposed here is more explicit about the elevated temperatures involved.</item>
      </notes>
